alt_text: SELECT debates, PROJECT audiences of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is higher than 200, PROJECT affirmative sides of #REF #3, PROJECT people on #REF #4, PROJECT names of #REF #5

source_text: Show the names of people and the number of times they have been on the affirmative side of debates.
output_text: SELECT people, PROJECT debates of #REF #1, PROJECT sides of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is affirmative, PROJECT names of #REF #4, GROUP count #4 #5, UNION #5 #6
alt_text: SELECT people, PROJECT debates of #REF #1, PROJECT side of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is affirmative, PROJECT names of #REF #4, GROUP count #4 #5, UNION #5 #6

source_text: Show the names of people who have been on the negative side of debates at least twice.

source_text: List the names of people that have not been on the affirmative side of debates.
output_text: SELECT debates, PROJECT sides of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is affirmative, DISCARD #1 #3, PROJECT names of #REF #4
alt_text: SELECT debates, PROJECT side of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is affirmative, DISCARD #1 #3, PROJECT names of #REF #4

source_text: Find the checking balance of the accounts whose savings balance is higher than the average savings balance.

alt_text: SELECT accounts, PROJECT savings balances of #REF #1, GROUP avg #2 #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is higher than #3, PROJECT checking balances of #REF #4

source_text: What are the balances of checking accounts belonging to people with savings balances greater than the average savings balance?

alt_text: SELECT wrestler, PROJECT names of #REF #1, PROJECT locations of #REF #1, UNION #2 #3

source_text: What are the names of wrestlers and their teams in elimination, ordered descending by days held?

alt_text: SELECT rooms, PROJECT decor of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is traditional, PROJECT bed type of #REF #3, PROJECT names of #REF #3, UNION #4 #5

source_text: Find the number of rooms with king bed for each decor type.
output_text: SELECT decor types, PROJECT rooms of #REF #1, FILTER #2 with king beds, GROUP count #3 #1, UNION #1 #4
alt_text: SELECT decor types, PROJECT rooms of #REF #1, PROJECT beds of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #2 #3 is king, AGGREGATE count #4

source_text: How many rooms have king beds? Report the number for each decor type.
output_text: SELECT rooms, FILTER #1 with king beds, PROJECT decor types of #REF #2, GROUP count #2 #3, UNION #3 #4
alt_text: SELECT rooms, FILTER #1 that have king beds, PROJECT decor types of #REF #2, GROUP count #2 #3, UNION #3 #4

source_text: Please show the nominee who has been nominated the greatest number of times.

alt_text: SELECT nominees, PROJECT times nominated of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, SUPERLATIVE max #1 #3

source_text: Find the average and minimum price of the rooms in different decor.

alt_text: SELECT rooms, PROJECT decor of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is different, PROJECT prices of #REF #3, GROUP avg #4 #3, AGGREGATE min #4, UNION #5 #6

source_text: What is the average minimum and price of the rooms for each different decor.

alt_text: SELECT different decors, PROJECT rooms of #REF #1, PROJECT prices of #REF #2, GROUP avg #3 #1, AGGREGATE min #4, UNION #5 #6

source_text: Find the name of the product that has the smallest capacity.

alt_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT departments of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is Finance, PROJECT first names of #REF #3, PROJECT job id of #REF #3, UNION #4 #5

source_text: display all the information of the employees whose salary if within the range of smallest salary and 2500.
output_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT salaries of #REF #1, AGGREGATE min #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is at least 2500, PROJECT information of #REF #3
alt_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT salaries of #REF #1, AGGREGATE min #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is equal to 2500, PROJECT information of #REF #4

source_text: What is all the information regarding employees with salaries above the minimum and under 2500?
output_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT salaries of #REF #1, AGGREGATE min #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is higher than #3, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is lower than 2500, INTERSECTION #1 #4 #5, PROJECT information regarding #REF #6
alt_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT salaries of #REF #1, AGGREGATE min #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is higher than #3, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is lower than 2500, INTERSECTION #1 #4 #5, PROJECT all information regarding #REF #6

source_text: Find the ids of the employees who does not work in those departments where some employees works whose manager id within the range 100 and 200.
output_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT managers of #REF #1, PROJECT ids of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at least 100, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at most 200, DISCARD #1 #4, PROJECT departments of #REF #5, PROJECT departments of #REF #6, PROJECT employees who work in #REF #7, DISCARD #8 #9, PROJECT ids of #REF #10
alt_text: SELECT employees, PROJECT managers of #REF #1, PROJECT ids of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at least 100, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at most 200, DISCARD #1 #4, PROJECT departments of #REF #5, PROJECT departments of #REF #6, PROJECT employees of #REF #7, DISCARD #8 #9, PROJECT ids of #REF #10

source_text: What are the ids for employees who do not work in departments with managers that have ids between 100 and 200?
output_text: SELECT departments, PROJECT managers of #REF #1, PROJECT ids of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at least 100, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at most 200, DISCARD #1 #4, PROJECT employees of #REF #5, PROJECT ids of #REF #6
alt_text: SELECT departments, PROJECT managers of #REF #1, PROJECT ids of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is lower than 100, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is lower than 200, DISCARD #1 #4, PROJECT employees of #REF #5, PROJECT ids of #REF #6

source_text: display the employee name ( first name and last name ) and hire date for all employees in the same department as Clara.

source_text: What is the count of the songs that last approximately 4 minutes?
output_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT minutes of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is approximately 4, AGGREGATE count #3
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT mins of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is approximately 4, AGGREGATE count #3

source_text: How many artists are from Bangladesh?
output_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 from Bangladesh, AGGREGATE count #2
alt_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 who are from Bangladesh, AGGREGATE count #2

source_text: How many Bangladeshi artists are listed?
output_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 that are Bangladeshi, AGGREGATE count #2
alt_text: SELECT Bangladeshi artists, AGGREGATE count #1

source_text: What is the average rating of songs produced by female artists?
output_text: SELECT songs, FILTER #1 produced by female artists, PROJECT ratings of #REF #2, AGGREGATE avg #3
alt_text: SELECT songs, FILTER #1 produced by female artists, PROJECT ratings of #REF #2, GROUP avg #3 #2, UNION #2 #4

source_text: Show the id and name of the aircraft with the maximum distance.
output_text: SELECT aircraft, PROJECT distances of #REF #1, SUPERLATIVE max #1 #2, PROJECT id of #REF #3, PROJECT name of #REF #3, UNION #4 #5
alt_text: SELECT aircraft, PROJECT distances of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is maximum, PROJECT id of #REF #3, PROJECT name of #REF #3, UNION #4 #5

source_text: How many songs, on average, are sung by a female artist?
output_text: SELECT female artists, PROJECT songs sung by #REF #1, AGGREGATE count #2
alt_text: SELECT songs, FILTER #1 sung by a female artist, AGGREGATE count #2

source_text: What is the most popular file format?
output_text: SELECT file formats, PROJECT most popular #REF #1
alt_text: SELECT file formats, PROJECT most popular of #REF #1

source_text: Find the file format that is used by the most files.
output_text: SELECT file formats, PROJECT files of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, SUPERLATIVE max #1 #3
alt_text: SELECT files, PROJECT file formats of #REF #1, GROUP count #1 #2, SUPERLATIVE max #2 #3

source_text: Find the names of the artists who are from UK and have produced English songs.
output_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 from UK, FILTER #2 who have produced English songs, PROJECT names of #REF #3
alt_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 from UK, FILTER #2 who have produced English songs, PROJECT names of #REF #3.

source_text: What are the names of the artists that are from the UK and sang songs in English?
output_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 from the UK, PROJECT songs #REF sang #2, FILTER #3 that are in English, PROJECT names of #REF #4
alt_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 from the UK, PROJECT songs #REF sang #2, COMPARATIVE #2 #3 is in English, PROJECT names of #REF #4

source_text: Find the id of songs that are available in mp4 format and have resolution lower than 1000.
output_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp4, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #3, COMPARATIVE #3 #4 is lower than 1000, PROJECT ids of #REF #5
alt_text: SELECT songs, FILTER #1 that are available in mp4 format, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #2 #3 is lower than 1000, PROJECT ids of #REF #4

source_text: What is the id of the files that are available in the format of mp4 and a resolution smaller than 1000?
output_text: SELECT files, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp4, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #4 is lower than 1000, INTERSECTION #1 #3 #5, PROJECT ids of #REF #6
alt_text: SELECT files, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp4, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is lower than 1000, INTERSECTION #1 #4 #5, PROJECT ids of #REF #6

source_text: What is the country of origin of the artist who is female and produced a song in Bangla?
output_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 who are female, PROJECT songs produced of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #2 #3 is Bangla, PROJECT country of origin of #REF #4
alt_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 who is female, FILTER #2 who produced a song in Bangla, PROJECT country of origin of #REF #3

source_text: What countries are the female artists who sung in the language Bangla from?
output_text: SELECT female artists, FILTER #1 who sung in the language Bangla, PROJECT countries of #REF #2
alt_text: SELECT female artists, PROJECT languages of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is Bangla, PROJECT countries of #REF #3

source_text: What is the average duration of songs that have mp3 format and resolution below 800?
output_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp3, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #4 is lower than 800, INTERSECTION #1 #3 #5, PROJECT durations of #REF #6, AGGREGATE avg #7
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp3, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #4 is below 800, INTERSECTION #1 #3 #5, PROJECT durations of #REF #6, AGGREGATE avg #7

source_text: What is the id and name of the aircraft that can cover the maximum distance?
output_text: SELECT aircraft, PROJECT distances #REF can cover #1, SUPERLATIVE max #1 #2, PROJECT id of #REF #3, PROJECT name of #REF #3, UNION #4 #5
alt_text: SELECT aircraft, PROJECT distances #REF can cover #1, SUPERLATIVE max #1 #2, PROJECT id of #REF #3, PROJECT name of #REF #3, UNION #4 #6

source_text: What is the average song duration for the songs that are in mp3 format and whose resolution below 800?
output_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp3, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #4 is lower than 800, PROJECT song durations of #REF #5, AGGREGATE avg #6
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT formats of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is mp3, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #4 is lower than 800, PROJECT durations of #REF #5, AGGREGATE avg #6

source_text: What is the number of artists for each gender?
output_text: SELECT genders, PROJECT artists of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, UNION #1 #3
alt_text: SELECT artists, PROJECT genders of #REF #1, GROUP count #1 #2, UNION #2 #3

source_text: How many artists are male and how many are female?
output_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 that are male, FILTER #1 that are female, AGGREGATE count #2, AGGREGATE count #3, ARITHMETIC sum #4 #5
alt_text: SELECT artists, FILTER #1 that are male, FILTER #1 that are female, AGGREGATE count #2, AGGREGATE count #3, UNION #4 #5

source_text: What is the average rating of songs for each language?
output_text: SELECT languages, PROJECT songs of #REF #1, PROJECT ratings of #REF #2, GROUP avg #3 #1, UNION #1 #4
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT languages of #REF #1, PROJECT ratings of #REF #1, GROUP avg #3 #2, UNION #2 #4

source_text: What is the average song rating for each language?
output_text: SELECT languages, PROJECT songs of #REF #1, PROJECT ratings of #REF #2, GROUP avg #3 #1, UNION #1 #4
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT languages of #REF #1, PROJECT ratings of #REF #1, GROUP avg #3 #2, UNION #2 #4

source_text: Return the gender and name of artist who produced the song with the lowest resolution.
output_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, SUPERLATIVE min #1 #2, PROJECT artist who produced #REF #3, PROJECT gender of #REF #4, PROJECT name of #REF #4, UNION #5 #6
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #2 is the lowest, PROJECT artist who produced #REF #3, PROJECT gender of #REF #4, PROJECT name of #REF #4, UNION #5 #6

source_text: What is the gender and name of the artist who sang the song with the smallest resolution?
output_text: SELECT artists, PROJECT songs of #REF #1, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #2, SUPERLATIVE min #1 #3, PROJECT gender of #REF #4, PROJECT name of #REF #4, UNION #5 #6
alt_text: SELECT songs, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #1, SUPERLATIVE min #1 #2, PROJECT artist who sang #REF #3, PROJECT gender of #REF #4, PROJECT name of #REF #4, UNION #5 #6

source_text: For each file format, return the number of artists who released songs in that format.
output_text: SELECT file formats, PROJECT artists who released songs in #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, UNION #1 #3
alt_text: SELECT file formats, PROJECT artists of #REF #1, FILTER #2 who released songs in that format, GROUP count #3 #1, UNION #1 #4

source_text: How many songs were released for each format?
output_text: SELECT formats, PROJECT songs released for #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, UNION #1 #3
alt_text: SELECT formats, PROJECT songs released for #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, UNION #1 #4

source_text: Find the distinct names of all songs that have a higher resolution than some songs in English.
output_text: SELECT songs, FILTER #1 in English, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #2, COMPARATIVE #2 #3 is higher than #4, PROJECT distinct names of #REF #5
alt_text: SELECT songs, FILTER #1 in English, PROJECT resolutions of #REF #2, AGGREGATE min #3, COMPARATIVE #2 #3 is higher than #4, PROJECT distinct names of #REF #5
